The Jews therefore who tell our Saviour here, that “ when Christ cometh, no man knoweth whence he is,” whether they knew him to have been born at Bethlehem or no, yet by his wonderful works they conceive this to have been the second manifestation of himself: and therefore only doubt whether he should be the Messiah or no, because they knew the place [Nazareth] from whence he came3 having been taught by tradition, that Messiah should come the second time from a place perfectly unknown to all men.
